      {
        image: "/images/projects/Puzleton/puzleton-3.webp",
        alt: "Spread one — the letter",
        caption: "Spread one — the letter",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/Puzleton/puzleton-4.webp",
        alt: "Spread two — the message",
        caption: "Spread two — the message",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/Puzleton/puzleton-5.webp",
        alt: "Spread three — the answer",
        caption: "Spread three — the answer",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/Puzleton/puzleton-6.webp",
        alt: "Spread four — wit",
        caption: "Spread four — wit",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/Puzleton/puzleton-7.webp",
        alt: "Spread five — steps",
        caption: "Spread five — steps",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/Puzleton/puzleton-8.webp",
        alt: "Spread six — coordinate",
        caption: "Spread six — coordinate",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/Puzleton/puzleton-9.webp",
        alt: "Spread seven — lost",
        caption: "Spread seven — lost",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/Puzleton/puzleton-10.webp",
        alt: "Spread eight — riddle",
        caption: "Spread eight — riddle",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/Puzleton/puzleton-11.webp",
        alt: "Spread nine — dots",
        caption: "Spread nine — dots",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/Puzleton/puzleton-12.webp",
        alt: "Spread ten — end",
        caption: "Spread ten — end",
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    id: "p-letter-abstraction",
    title: "P — Letter Abstraction",
    type: "graphic",
    kind: "case-study",
    thumb: "/images/projects/P/p-thumb.webp",
    tools: ["Illustrator"],
    slides: [
      {
        image: "/images/projects/P/p-1.webp",
        alt: "Project overview",
        label: "Overview",
        heading: "Brief",
        body: "For this project, I was challenged with taking a letter of the alphabet, randomly assigned, and to identify the most base characteristics in its anatomy so that it was still recognizable after a major abstraction.",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/P/p-2.webp",
        alt: "Research",
        label: "Research",
        heading: "Initial sketching",
        body: "The process started with volume—sketches pushing the letter in as many directions as I thought were interesting before committing to anything. Early rounds tested both blocky and geometric interpretations and looser, more organic ones. I deliberately keept the range wide to avoid locking in too soon.",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/P/p-3.webp",
        alt: "Research",
        label: "Research",
        heading: "Initial sketching",
        body: "With a clearer sense of direction, I started getting a bit more specific. Two questions: does the counter stay or go, and how far can the stem be manipulated before the 'P' stops reading? A second thread pushed toward a fuller abstraction leaning into fluidity and shape over strict letterform anatomy to find where the letter's recognition begins to break down.",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/P/p-4.webp",
        alt: "Process",
        label: "Process",
        heading: "Iteration!",
        body: "I began testing the same core idea across a spectrum of treatments, from blocky and geometric to round and fluid. I tried adding counters to parts of the letterform where they don't typically live. The stem became another variable, kept in some versions, removed in others, to see how much structural information the 'P' actually needs to stay legible.",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/P/p-5.webp",
        alt: "Iteration",
        label: "Process",
        heading: "Contenders",
        body: "Two finalists went to critique—and the blocky, counter-heavy version on the left won by a wide margin. But it wasn't quite done. The composition still felt slightly off-balance.",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/P/p-6.webp",
        alt: "refine",
        label: "Refine",
        heading: "Balancing out",
        body: "The refinement phase focused on balance. I measured with overlaid circles, which wasn't the most efficient method, but it felt right!.",
      },
      {
        image: "/images/projects/P/p-7.webp",
        alt: "final design",
        label: "Outcome",
        heading: "Final design",
        body: "The final design stands in both light and dark—the 'P' is still unmistakably there, stripped down to just enough: the bowl, the stem replaced by three circles, the counter doing the heavy lifting.",
      },
